results.name: Largest number of crossing-free matchings on a set S of n points in the plane, that is, a set of floor(n/2) pairwise non-intersecting segments with endpoints in S having no endpoint in common.
link: O. Aichholzer and H. Krasser, The point set order type data base: a collection of applications and results, pp. 17-20 in Abstracts 13th Canadian Conference on Computational Geometry (CCCG '01), Waterloo, Aug. 13-15, 2001.
M. Sharir and E. Welzl. On the Number of Crossing-Free Matchings, (Cycles, and Partitions)
example: The Sharir link contains an image (Figure 1) of a placement of 6 points in the plane such that 12 of their perfect matchings are crossing-free, demonstrating that a(6) >= 12. - _Nathaniel Johnston_, Nov 17 2014
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Aug 14 2001
